Yes, one's first operating system is always the best.

Orientals were self-handicapped by not having a smaller alphabet.
Horrible typewriters, and forget putting the glyphs into a
mid-80's character ROM.  Yes, they're concise, but they
require very high resolution to render.  And, at least some
symbol sets are not phonetic.

